name: Intl.Collator
description: Constructor for collators, which are objects that enable language-sensitive string comparison.

parameters.name: Intl.Collator()
parameters.description: Creates a new Collator object.

parameters.name: Intl.Collator.supportedLocalesOf()
parameters.description: Returns an array containing those of the provided locales that are supported without having to fall back to the runtime's default locale.

parameters.name: Intl.Collator.prototype.constructor
parameters.description: The constructor function that created the instance object. For Intl.Collator instances, the initial value is the Intl.Collator constructor.

parameters.name: Intl.Collator.prototype[@@toStringTag]
parameters.description: The initial value of the @@toStringTag property is the string "Intl.Collator". This property is used in Object.prototype.toString().

parameters.name: Intl.Collator.prototype.compare()
parameters.description: Getter function that compares two strings according to the sort order of this Intl.Collator object.

parameters.name: Intl.Collator.prototype.resolvedOptions()
parameters.description: Returns a new object with properties reflecting the locale and collation options computed during initialization of the object.

name: Intl.DateTimeFormat
description: Constructor for objects that enable language-sensitive date and time formatting.

parameters.name: Intl.DateTimeFormat()
parameters.description: Creates a new Intl.DateTimeFormat object.

parameters.name: Intl.DateTimeFormat.supportedLocalesOf()
parameters.description: Returns an array containing those of the provided locales that are supported without having to fall back to the runtime's default locale.

parameters.name: Intl.DateTimeFormat.prototype.constructor
parameters.description: The constructor function that created the instance object. For Intl.DateTimeFormat instances, the initial value is the Intl.DateTimeFormat constructor.

parameters.name: Intl.DateTimeFormat.prototype[@@toStringTag]
parameters.description: The initial value of the @@toStringTag property is the string "Intl.DateTimeFormat". This property is used in Object.prototype.toString().

parameters.name: Intl.DateTimeFormat.prototype.format()
parameters.description: Getter function that formats a date according to the locale and formatting options of this DateTimeFormat object.

parameters.name: Intl.DateTimeFormat.prototype.formatRange()
parameters.description: This method receives two Dates and formats the date range in the most concise way based on the locale and options provided when instantiating DateTimeFormat.

parameters.name: Intl.DateTimeFormat.prototype.formatRangeToParts()
parameters.description: This method receives two Dates and returns an Array of objects containing the locale-specific tokens representing each part of the formatted date range.

parameters.name: Intl.DateTimeFormat.prototype.formatToParts()
parameters.description: Returns an Array of objects representing the date string in parts that can be used for custom locale-aware formatting.

parameters.name: Intl.DateTimeFormat.prototype.resolvedOptions()
parameters.description: Returns a new object with properties reflecting the locale and formatting options computed during initialization of the object.

name: Intl.Locale
description: Constructor for objects that represents a Unicode locale identifier.

parameters.name: Intl.Locale()
parameters.description: Creates a new Locale object.

parameters.name: Intl.Locale.prototype.baseName
parameters.description: Returns basic, core information about the Locale in the form of a substring of the complete data string.

parameters.name: Intl.Locale.prototype.calendar
parameters.description: Returns the part of the Locale that indicates the Locale's calendar era.

parameters.name: Intl.Locale.prototype.caseFirst
parameters.description: Returns whether case is taken into account for the locale's collation rules.

parameters.name: Intl.Locale.prototype.collation
parameters.description: Returns the collation type for the Locale, which is used to order strings according to the locale's rules.

parameters.name: Intl.Locale.prototype.constructor
parameters.description: The constructor function that created the instance object. For Intl.Locale instances, the initial value is the Intl.Locale constructor.

parameters.name: Intl.Locale.prototype.hourCycle
parameters.description: Returns the time keeping format convention used by the locale.

parameters.name: Intl.Locale.prototype.language
parameters.description: Returns the language associated with the locale.

parameters.name: Intl.Locale.prototype.numberingSystem
parameters.description: Returns the numeral system used by the locale.

parameters.name: Intl.Locale.prototype.numeric
parameters.description: Returns whether the locale has special collation handling for numeric characters.

parameters.name: Intl.Locale.prototype.region
parameters.description: Returns the region of the world (usually a country) associated with the locale.

parameters.name: Intl.Locale.prototype.script
parameters.description: Returns the script used for writing the particular language used in the locale.

parameters.name: Intl.Locale.prototype[@@toStringTag]
parameters.description: The initial value of the @@toStringTag property is the string "Intl.Locale". This property is used in Object.prototype.toString().

parameters.name: Intl.Locale.prototype.getCalendars()
parameters.description: Returns an Array of available calendar identifiers, according to the locale's rules.

parameters.name: Intl.Locale.prototype.getCollations()
parameters.description: Returns an Array of the collation types for the Locale.

parameters.name: Intl.Locale.prototype.getHourCycles()
parameters.description: Returns an Array of hour cycle identifiers, indicating either the 12-hour clock ("h12"), the Japanese 12-hour clock ("h11"), the 24-hour clock ("h23"), or the unused format "h24".

parameters.name: Intl.Locale.prototype.getNumberingSystems()
parameters.description: Returns an Array of numbering system identifiers available according to the locale's rules.

parameters.name: Intl.Locale.prototype.getTextInfo()
parameters.description: Returns the part indicating the ordering of characters ltr (left-to-right) or rtl (right-to-left).

parameters.name: Intl.Locale.prototype.getTimeZones()
parameters.description: Returns an Array of time zone identifiers, associated with the Locale.

parameters.name: Intl.Locale.prototype.getWeekInfo()
parameters.description: Returns UTS 35's Week Elements according to the locale rules.

parameters.name: Intl.Locale.prototype.maximize()
parameters.description: Gets the most likely values for the language, script, and region of the locale based on existing values.

parameters.name: Intl.Locale.prototype.minimize()
parameters.description: Attempts to remove information about the locale that would be added by calling maximize().

parameters.name: Intl.Locale.prototype.toString()
parameters.description: Returns the Locale's full locale identifier string.

name: Intl.getCanonicalLocales()
return_value: An array containing the canonical locale names.

parameters.name: locales
parameters.description: A list of String values for which to get the canonical locale names.

name: Intl.supportedValuesOf()
description: Returns a sorted array containing the supported unique calendar, collation, currency, numbering systems, or unit values supported by the implementation.
return_value: A sorted array of unique string values indicating the values supported by the implementation for the given key.

parameters.name: key
parameters.description: A key string indicating the category of values to be returned. This is one of: "calendar", "collation", "currency", "numberingSystem", "timeZone", "unit".

parameters.name: RangeError
parameters.description: Thrown if an unsupported key was passed as a parameter.
